{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846209006,"sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","part":{"id":"prt_d78aeb5b7001BzpCX7X1IRuMUA","messageID":"msg_d78ae7b9500168dmDFvioVDWFX","sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d979265c1f934a328484ba94372aa91a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775846208987,"end":1775846209004}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846209013,"sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","part":{"id":"prt_d78aea5d1001MqrrBNfTkUDgIF","messageID":"msg_d78ae7b9500168dmDFvioVDWFX","sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6eda63d2b8f9421f89b7ee08687e8b37","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement sandbox deletion handlers, garbage collection loop, and lifecycle management in the workload manager. This AR completes the sandbox lifecycle by adding:\n6: \n7: 1. **Delete Handlers**: HTTP handlers for `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` that remove Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs and clean up session metadata from the Store\n8: \n9: 2. **Garbage Collection Loop**: Background goroutine that periodically scans for expired and inactive sandboxes, deleting stale resources to prevent resource leaks\n10: \n11: 3. **Graceful Shutdown**: Process lifecycle management with SIGINT/SIGTERM signal handling, HTTP server graceful shutdown, informer stop, and Store cleanup\n12: \n13: Core responsibilities:\n14: - **Session Lookup**: Retrieve `SandboxInfo` from Store by `sessionId`, return 404 if not found\n15: - **CR Deletion**: Delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim based on stored `Kind` field using dynamic client\n16: - **GC Loop**: Tick every 15 seconds, query expired sessions (TTL passed) and inactive sessions (idle timeout), batch delete up to 16 per tick\n17: - **Graceful Shutdown**: Cancel background workers, shutdown HTTP within 15s, close Store connections\n18: \n19: ## Scope\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: | Deliverable | Description |\n24: |-------------|-------------|\n25: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/delete.go` | HTTP delete handlers: `handleDeleteSandbox` for session-based sandbox deletion |\n26: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GC loop: tick-based scanning, expired/inactive detection, batch deletion |\n27: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | Process lifecycle: signal handling, graceful shutdown coordination |\n28: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` (update) | Integration: GC loop start, shutdown hook registration |\n29: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` (update) | Add `DeleteSandboxRequest`, `DeleteSandboxResponse` types if needed |\n30: | Test files | `*_test.go` for delete handlers, GC loop, lifecycle management |\n31: \n32: ### API Endpoints\n33: \n34: | Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n35: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n36: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n37: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID (shared handler) |\n38: \n39: ### Out of Scope\n40: \n41: - Sandbox creation handlers (AR-005)\n42: - Router deployment (`cmd/router`) and session routing\n43: - Agentd idle cleanup controller (`cmd/agentd`)\n44: - CRD type definitions (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n45: - client-go code generation\n46: - Helm chart and deployment manifests\n47: - E2E integration test fixtures\n48: \n49: ## Impact Analysis\n50: \n51: ### Upstream Dependencies\n52: \n53: | Dependency | Impact |\n54: |------------|--------|\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Not directly used for delete; dynamic client handles Sandbox/SandboxClaim deletion |\n56: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs via `Delete` method with `metav1.DeleteOptions` |\n57: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | `IsNotFound` check for idempotent delete (treat NotFound as success) |\n58: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` (or Store interface) | `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListSandboxes` for session management |\n59: | `pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` struct with `Kind`, `ExpiresAt`, `LastActivity` fields |\n60: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | `DefaultSandboxTTL`, `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`, `SandboxDeleteTimeout`, `GarbageCollectorInterval` constants |\n61: \n62: ### Downstream Consumers\n63: \n64: | Consumer | Usage |\n65: |----------|-------|\n66: | Router (`cmd/router`) | Session cleanup affects routing table; deleted sessions are removed from routing cache |\n67: | Agentd (`cmd/agentd`) | GC loop reduces load on idle cleanup controller; complementary cleanup mechanisms |\n68: | Monitoring systems | GC metrics: deleted count, cleanup latency, error rate |\n69: | Kubernetes cluster | Resource cleanup prevents orphaned Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs |\n70: | Auth middleware | Per-user dynamic client context (`EnableAuth=true`) affects delete operations |\n71: \n72: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n73: \n74: - **Delete Response Format**: `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}` must remain stable\n75: - **404 Response Format**: `{\"message\":\"Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted\"}` format documented\n76: - **GC Constants**: `GarbageCollectorInterval = 2 minutes`, `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 minutes` are spec-required\n77: - **Kind Field Tracking**: `SandboxInfo.Kind` determines GVR for delete; must be populated correctly during creation (AR-005)\n78: - **Shutdown Timeout**: 15-second HTTP shutdown is spec-required\n79: \n80: ## Alternatives Considered\n81: \n82: ### Alternative 1: Separate Delete Handlers per Kind\n83: \n84: **Approach**: Use distinct handlers for AgentRuntime vs CodeInterpreter delete endpoints.\n85: \n86: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n87: |--------|------------|\n88: | Pros | Clearer separation; route-specific logging |\n89: | Cons | Duplicated session lookup logic; both use same Store and CR deletion; spec requires shared handler |\n90: \n91: **Decision**: Rejected. Both endpoints use identical session lookup and CR deletion logic. The `Kind` field in `SandboxInfo` already distinguishes Sandbox vs SandboxClaim.\n92: \n93: ### Alternative 2: Polling GC Instead of Tick-Based\n94: \n95: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes informer events to trigger GC on Sandbox/SandboxClaim deletion.\n96: \n97: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n98: |--------|------------|\n99: | Pros | Event-driven; immediate cleanup; lower latency |\n100: | Cons | Requires informer for external CRDs (Sandbox/SandboxClaim); GC also needs Store cleanup; event may miss Store-only entries |\n101: \n102: **Decision**: Rejected. Tick-based GC handles both CR cleanup and Store cleanup uniformly. Informer-based approach would require additional client-go code generation for external CRDs.\n103: \n104: ### Alternative 3: Immediate Delete Without Store Cleanup\n105: \n106: **Approach**: Delete CR only; rely on Store TTL or separate cleanup process.\n107: \n108: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n109: |--------|------------|\n110: | Pros | Faster delete handler; simpler implementation |\n111: | Cons | Store entries orphaned; GC would need to detect CR-missing entries; inconsistent state between Store and K8s |\n112: \n113: **Decision**: Rejected. Delete handler must clean both CR and Store for consistent state. This matches the creation pattern where Store placeholder is written before CR.\n114: \n115: ### Alternative 4: GC Loop in Separate Process\n116: \n117: **Approach**: Run GC as a separate `cmd/gc` binary for dedicated cleanup.\n118: \n119: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n120: |--------|------------|\n121: | Pros | Independent scaling; isolated failure domain |\n122: | Cons | Requires shared Store access; coordination complexity; spec requires GC in workload manager |\n123: \n124: **Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires GC loop in workload manager process. This enables coordinated shutdown and shared Store connection.\n125: \n126: ### Alternative 5: Delete via controller-runtime Reconciler\n127: \n128: **Approach**: Use controller-runtime to watch Store entries and reconcile deletions.\n129: \n130: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n131: |--------|------------|\n132: | Pros | Declarative pattern; automatic retry; status tracking |\n133: | Cons | Over-engineering for simple delete operation; Store is not a K8s resource; requires custom reconciler logic |\n134: \n135: **Decision**: Rejected. Direct HTTP handler + tick-based GC is simpler and matches the spec pattern.\n136: \n137: ## Risks\n138: \n139: | Risk | Mitigation |\n140: |------|------------|\n141: | Store unavailable during delete | Ping store at startup; return 503 on Store errors; GC retries on next tick |\n142: | CR deletion fails (network/API error) | Use 30s timeout context; log error; GC retries on next tick |\n143: | Race condition: GC deletes while user delete in progress | Store placeholder as lock; check CR existence before GC delete |\n144: | Session ID format mismatch (UUID vs custom) | Store lookup by exact key; validate UUID format in handler (optional) |\n145: | Graceful shutdown timeout exceeded | 15s HTTP shutdown; background workers get context cancellation; log if shutdown incomplete |\n146: | GC batch size too large (memory pressure) | Limit to 16 per tick per spec; log if more pending |\n147: | Informer cache stale for Pod lookup (if needed) | Not used in delete; GC uses Store timestamps only |\n148: | Per-user client context missing when `EnableAuth=true` | Validate context keys; fallback to default client with warning |\n149: \n150: ## Implementation Notes\n151: \n152: 1. **Delete Handler Flow**:\n153:    ```\n154:    1. Extract sessionId from chi.URLParam\n155:    2. Store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionId)\n156:    3. If ErrNotFound → 404 response\n157:    4. Determine GVR: SandboxInfo.Kind == \"SandboxClaim\" → SandboxClaimGVR, else SandboxGVR\n158:    5. dynamicClient.Delete(ctx, GVR, namespace, sandboxName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n159:    6. If IsNotFound → treat as success (already deleted)\n160:    7. Store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionId)\n161:    8. Return 200 {\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}\n162:    ```\n163: \n164: 2. **GC Loop Flow**:\n165:    ```\n166:    1. Tick every GarbageCollectorInterval (2 minutes per spec, 15s tick per another spec)\n167:    2. Context timeout 2 minutes per tick\n168:    3. Query inactive: cutoff = now - DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout (15m)\n169:    4. Query expired: cutoff = now (ExpiresAt < now)\n170:    5. Merge unique sessions, limit batch to 16\n171:    6. For each: delete CR → delete Store entry\n172:    7. Continue next tick\n173:    ```\n174: \n175: 3. **Graceful Shutdown Flow**:\n176:    ```\n177:    1. Register signal handler (SIGINT, SIGTERM)\n178:    2. On signal: cancel main context\n179:    3. httpServer.Shutdown(ctx with 15s timeout)\n180:    4. Wait for background workers (GC loop, informers)\n181:    5. Store.Close()\n182:    6. Exit\n183:    ```\n184: \n185: 4. **GVR Constants** (from defaults.go):\n186:    ```go\n187:    SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\n188:    SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n189:    ```\n190: \n191: 5. **Timeout Configuration**:\n192:    ```go\n193:    SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second  // per CR delete\n194:    GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute   // GC tick interval\n195:    DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute  // inactive cutoff\n196:    DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour     // expiration cutoff\n197:    HTTPShutdownTimeout       = 15 * time.Second  // graceful shutdown\n198:    ```\n199: \n200: 6. **Error Response Format**: All errors use `{\"message\": \"...\"}` per spec.\n201: \n202: 7. **Idempotent Delete**: `IsNotFound` errors from K8s API are treated as success (sandbox already deleted).\n203: \n204: 8. **Per-User Client**: When `EnableAuth=true`, use context-injected dynamic client; fallback to default client.\n205: \n206: ## References\n207: \n208: - Spec: `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` (Delete sandbox by session, Garbage collection loop, HTTP server behavior)\n209: - Spec: `idle-cleanup/spec.md` (Idle detection pattern, SessionExpirationTimeout)\n210: - Design: `changes/AR-006/design.md`\n211: - client-go Reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n212: - Defaults: `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n213: - Store Interface: `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` (Store interface)\n214: - SandboxInfo: `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`\n215: - AR-005 Proposal: `changes/AR-005/proposal.md` (Creation pattern, Kind field tracking)\n216: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n217: - agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n\n(End of file - total 217 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement sandbox deletion handlers, garbage collection loop, and lifecycle management in the workload manager. This AR completes the sandbox lifecycle by adding:\n\n1. **Delete Handlers**: HTTP handlers for `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` that remove Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs and clean up session metadata from the Store\n\n2. **Garbage Collection Loop**: Background goroutine that periodically scans for expired and inactive sandboxes, deleting stale resources to prevent resource leaks\n\n3. **Graceful Shutdown**: Process lifecycle management with SIGINT/SIGTERM signal handling, HTTP server graceful shutdown, informer stop, and Store cleanup\n\nCore responsibilities:\n- **Session Lookup**: Retrieve `SandboxInfo` from Store by `sessionId`, return 404 if not found\n- **CR Deletion**: Delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim based on stored `Kind` field using dynamic client\n- **GC Loop**: Tick every 15 seconds, query expired sessions (TTL passed) and inactive sessions (idle timeout), batch delete up to 16 per tick\n- **Graceful Shutdown**: Cancel background workers, shutdown HTTP within 15s, close Store connections\n\n## Scope\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775846208978,"end":1775846209011}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846209015,"sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","part":{"id":"prt_d78aea9fa00155BUau12VZz6e5","messageID":"msg_d78ae7b9500168dmDFvioVDWFX","sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-479d93dff7f04bc8a6e180e30548d1ce","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: [待填写: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理的范围定义]\n16: \n17: ## Out of Scope\n18: \n19: - [待填写]\n20: \n21: ## Dependencies\n22: \n23: - [待填写]\n24: \n25: ## Deliverables\n26: \n27: | File | Description |\n28: |------|-------------|\n29: | [待填写] | [待填写] |\n30: \n31: ## Acceptance Criteria\n32: \n33: - [ ] [待填写]\n34: \n35: ## References\n36: \n37: - [待填写]\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\n[待填写: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理的范围定义]\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- [待填写]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/spec.md","time":{"start":1775846208982,"end":1775846209014}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846209017,"sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","part":{"id":"prt_d78aeaddf001IURYg0jQ05T1pg","messageID":"msg_d78ae7b9500168dmDFvioVDWFX","sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c86e2067b7744941bac2eeb5297a79ee","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 实现 Sandbox 删除处理器及生命周期管理机制，包括：\n14: - 删除 Sandbox CR 及关联资源（Pod、ServiceAccount 等）\n15: - TTL 过期清理、Idle timeout 检测、Max session duration 限制\n16: - Garbage Collector 定期清理失效 Sandbox\n17: - 与 agentd 的 idle cleanup 协调\n18: \n19: ## Design\n20: \n21: ### Architecture\n22: \n23: ```\n24: pkg/workloadmanager/\n25: ├── lifecycle.go              — Sandbox 生命周期管理核心逻辑\n26: ├── lifecycle_test.go         — 生命周期测试\n27: ├── garbage_collector.go      — GC 定期清理器\n28: ├── garbage_collector_test.go — GC 测试\n29: ├── deletion_handler.go       — DELETE /v1/{kind}/sessions/:sessionId 处理器\n30: ├── deletion_handler_test.go  — 删除处理器测试\n31: ├── k8s_client.go             — (existing) K8sClient 扩展删除方法\n32: ├── types.go                  — (existing) Store interface、错误类型\n33: ├── defaults.go               — (existing) TTL/Timeout 常量\n34: └── handlers/\n35:     └── sandbox_delete.go     — Sandbox 删除 HTTP handler\n36: ```\n37: \n38: **组件交互图：**\n39: \n40: ```\n41: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n42: │  HTTP DELETE    │────▶│  DeletionHandler │────▶│    K8sClient    │\n43: │  /sessions/:id  │     │                  │     │  (dynamic client)│\n44: └─────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n45:                                │                        │\n46:                                ▼                        ▼\n47:                         ┌──────────────┐         ┌──────────────┐\n48:                         │    Store     │         │  Sandbox CR  │\n49:                         │ (Redis/Valkey│         │  + Pod SA    │\n50:                         └──────────────┘         └──────────────┘\n51: \n52: ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n53: │                    Garbage Collector (goroutine)              │\n54: │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────┐  │\n55: │  │ interval    │──▶│ ListExpired │──▶│ Delete Sandbox CR   │  │\n56: │  │ (2min tick) │   │ + Inactive  │   │ + cleanup Store     │  │\n57: │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────────────┘  │\n58: └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ### Dependencies\n62: \n63: | Package | Purpose |\n64: |---------|---------|\n65: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | 判断 NotFound、Conflict 等 K8s 错误 |\n66: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | DeleteOptions、GracePeriodSeconds |\n67: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Dynamic client 删除 Sandbox CR |\n68: | `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Sandbox 类型定义 |\n69: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo、Store interface |\n70: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n71: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Labels/Annotations 常量 |\n72: \n73: ### Integration with client-go\n74: \n75: client-go library (`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`) 提供：\n76: \n77: ```go\n78: import (\n79:     agentcubeclient \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n80:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n81: )\n82: \n83: type AgentCubeClient struct {\n84:     clientset agentcubeclient.Interface\n85: }\n86: \n87: func NewAgentCubeClient(config *rest.Config) (*AgentCubeClient, error) {\n88:     clientset, err := agentcubeclient.NewForConfig(config)\n89:     if err != nil {\n90:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create agentcube clientset: %w\", err)\n91:     }\n92:     return &AgentCubeClient{clientset: clientset}, nil\n93: }\n94: \n95: func (c *AgentCubeClient) AgentRuntimes(namespace string) runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInterface {\n96:     return c.clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace)\n97: }\n98: \n99: func (c *AgentCubeClient) CodeInterpreters(namespace string) runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInterface {\n100:     return c.clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace)\n101: }\n102: ```\n103: \n104: 用于查询 AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter 的 sessionTimeout/maxSessionDuration 配置。\n105: \n106: ## Data Structures\n107: \n108: ### DeleteSandboxRequest\n109: \n110: ```go\n111: type DeleteSandboxRequest struct {\n112:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n113:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\"` // \"agent-runtime\" or \"code-interpreter\"\n114: }\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ### DeleteSandboxResponse\n118: \n119: ```go\n120: type DeleteSandboxResponse struct {\n121:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n122:     Status    string `json:\"status\"` // \"deleted\" or \"deleting\"\n123:     Message   string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: ### LifecycleConfig\n128: \n129: ```go\n130: type LifecycleConfig struct {\n131:     DefaultTTL             time.Duration // 8h\n132:     DefaultIdleTimeout     time.Duration // 15m\n133:     DefaultMaxDuration     time.Duration // 8h\n134:     GCInterval             time.Duration // 2min\n135:     GCOnceTimeout          time.Duration // 2min\n136:     DeletionGracePeriod    int64         // 0 (immediate)\n137:     DeletionTimeout        time.Duration // 30s\n138: }\n139: ```\n140: \n141: ### SandboxLifecycleManager\n142: \n143: ```go\n144: type SandboxLifecycleManager struct {\n145:     k8sClient      *K8sClient\n146:     agentcubeClient *AgentCubeClient\n147:     store          Store\n148:     config         LifecycleConfig\n149:     logger         Logger\n150: }\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### GarbageCollector\n154: \n155: ```go\n156: type GarbageCollector struct {\n157:     manager    *SandboxLifecycleManager\n158:     interval   time.Duration\n159:     onceTimeout time.Duration\n160:     stopCh     chan struct{}\n161:     wg         sync.WaitGroup\n162: }\n163: \n164: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Start()\n165: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop()\n166: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runOnce(ctx context.Context) error\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ## API Endpoints\n170: \n171: ### DELETE `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`\n172: \n173: | Field | Value |\n174: |-------|-------|\n175: | Method | DELETE |\n176: | Path | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` |\n177: | Auth | If `EnableAuth` |\n178: | Handler | `handleDeleteAgentRuntimeSandbox` |\n179: \n180: **Response (200):**\n181: \n182: ```json\n183: {\n184:   \"sessionId\": \"abc-123\",\n185:   \"status\": \"deleted\"\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: **Response (404):**\n190: \n191: ```json\n192: {\n193:   \"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\",\n194:   \"message\": \"session not found: abc-123\"\n195: }\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### DELETE `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId`\n199: \n200: | Field | Value |\n201: |-------|-------|\n202: | Method | DELETE |\n203: | Path | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` |\n204: | Auth | If `EnableAuth` |\n205: | Handler | `handleDeleteCodeInterpreterSandbox` |\n206: \n207: **Response:** 同上\n208: \n209: ## Lifecycle Management Logic\n210: \n211: ### Delete Sandbox Flow\n212: \n213: ```go\n214: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) DeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n215:     // 1. Get sandbox info from store\n216:     sandboxInfo, err := m.store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n217:     if err != nil {\n218:         if errors.Is(err, ErrSandboxNotFound) {\n219:             return &NotFoundError{Resource: \"session\", Name: sessionID}\n220:         }\n221:         return &InternalError{Err: err}\n222:     }\n223: \n224:     // 2. Delete Sandbox CR via dynamic client\n225:     sandboxGVR := schema.GroupVersionResource{\n226:         Group:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n227:         Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n228:         Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n229:     }\n230: \n231:     deleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{\n232:         GracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To[int64](m.config.DeletionGracePeriod),\n233:     }\n234: \n235:     err = m.k8sClient.DynamicClient().Resource(sandboxGVR).\n236:         Namespace(sandboxInfo.SandboxNamespace).\n237:         Delete(ctx, sandboxInfo.SandboxName, deleteOpts)\n238:     \n239:     if err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n240:         return &InternalError{Err: fmt.Errorf(\"delete sandbox CR: %w\", err)}\n241:     }\n242: \n243:     // 3. If SandboxClaim was used, delete it too\n244:     if sandboxInfo.Kind == types.SandboxClaimKind {\n245:         claimGVR := schema.GroupVersionResource{\n246:             Group:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n247:             Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n248:             Resource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n249:         }\n250:         m.k8sClient.DynamicClient().Resource(claimGVR).\n251:             Namespace(sandboxInfo.SandboxNamespace).\n252:             Delete(ctx, sandboxInfo.SandboxName, deleteOpts)\n253:     }\n254: \n255:     // 4. Delete from store\n256:     err = m.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n257:     if err != nil {\n258:         m.logger.Error(\"failed to delete from store\", \"sessionID\", sessionID, \"err\", err)\n259:     }\n260: \n261:     return nil\n262: }\n263: ```\n264: \n265: ### TTL & Timeout Calculation\n266: \n267: ```go\n268: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) CalculateLifecycle(\n269:     kind string,\n270:     namespace string,\n271:     name string,\n272: ) (ttl, idleTimeout, maxDuration time.Duration, err error) {\n273:     \n274:     ttl = m.config.DefaultTTL\n275:     idleTimeout = m.config.DefaultIdleTimeout\n276:     maxDuration = m.config.DefaultMaxDuration\n277: \n278:     // Query AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter for configured values\n279:     switch kind {\n280:     case types.AgentRuntimeKind:\n281:         ar, err := m.agentcubeClient.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(\n282:             ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n283:         if err != nil {\n284:             if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n285:                 return // use defaults\n286:             }\n287:             return ttl, idleTimeout, maxDuration, err\n288:         }\n289:         if ar.Spec.SessionTimeout != nil {\n290:             idleTimeout = ar.Spec.SessionTimeout.Duration\n291:         }\n292:         if ar.Spec.MaxSessionDuration != nil {\n293:             maxDuration = ar.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration\n294:         }\n295:         ttl = maxDuration // TTL = max session duration\n296:         \n297:     case types.CodeInterpreterKind:\n298:         ci, err := m.agentcubeClient.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(\n299:             ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n300:         if err != nil {\n301:             if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n302:                 return // use defaults\n303:             }\n304:             return ttl, idleTimeout, maxDuration, err\n305:         }\n306:         if ci.Spec.SessionTimeout != nil {\n307:             idleTimeout = ci.Spec.SessionTimeout.Duration\n308:         }\n309:         if ci.Spec.MaxSessionDuration != nil {\n310:             maxDuration = ci.Spec.MaxSessionDuration.Duration\n311:         }\n312:         ttl = maxDuration\n313:     }\n314: \n315:     return ttl, idleTimeout, maxDuration, nil\n316: }\n317: ```\n318: \n319: ### Check Expiration\n320: \n321: ```go\n322: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) IsExpired(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) bool {\n323:     return time.Now().After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)\n324: }\n325: \n326: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) IsIdleExpired(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, idleTimeout time.Duration) bool {\n327:     if sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero() {\n328:         return false\n329:     }\n330:     return time.Now().After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))\n331: }\n332: ```\n333: \n334: ### Garbage Collection Algorithm\n335: \n336: ```go\n337: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runOnce(ctx context.Context) error {\n338:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)\n339:     defer cancel()\n340: \n341:     now := time.Now()\n342: \n343:     // 1. List expired sandboxes (TTL reached)\n344:     expired, err := gc.manager.store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, 16)\n345:     if err != nil {\n346:         return fmt.Errorf(\"list expired: %w\", err)\n347:     }\n348: \n349:     // 2. List inactive sandboxes (idle timeout reached)\n350:     inactiveBefore := now.Add(-gc.manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout)\n351:     inactive, err := gc.manager.store.ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, 16)\n352:     if err != nil {\n353:         return fmt.Errorf(\"list inactive: %w\", err)\n354:     }\n355: \n356:     // 3. Delete each sandbox\n357:     allSandboxes := append(expired, inactive...)\n358:     for _, sb := range allSandboxes {\n359:         if err := gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID); err != nil {\n360:             gc.manager.logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\",\n361:                 \"sessionID\", sb.SessionID, \"err\", err)\n362:             continue\n363:         }\n364:         gc.manager.logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\",\n365:             \"sessionID\", sb.SessionID,\n366:             \"reason\", determineReason(sb, now, inactiveBefore))\n367:     }\n368: \n369:     return nil\n370: }\n371: ```\n372: \n373: ## Error Handling\n374: \n375: ### Error Types\n376: \n377: | Error | HTTP Status | Code |\n378: |-------|-------------|------|\n379: | Session not found | 404 | `NOT_FOUND` |\n380: | Sandbox CR already deleted | 200 (success) | `deleted` |\n381: | K8s API error | 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` |\n382: | Store error | 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` |\n383: | Timeout during deletion | 503 | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` |\n384: \n385: ### Graceful Deletion Handling\n386: \n387: ```go\n388: func handleDeleteError(err error) error {\n389:     if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n390:         // Already deleted - treat as success\n391:         return nil\n392:     }\n393:     if apierrors.IsConflict(err) {\n394:         // Retry with force delete\n395:         return &ConflictError{Resource: \"sandbox\", Err: err}\n396:     }\n397:     return &InternalError{Err: err}\n398: }\n399: ```\n400: \n401: ### Force Delete (Last Resort)\n402: \n403: ```go\n404: func (m *SandboxLifecycleManager) ForceDeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n405:     sandboxInfo, err := m.store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n406:     if err != nil {\n407:         return err\n408:     }\n409: \n410:     deleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{\n411:         GracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To[int64](0),\n412:     }\n413: \n414:     // Use foreground deletion finalizer override\n415:     m.k8sClient.DynamicClient().Resource(sandboxGVR).\n416:         Namespace(sandboxInfo.SandboxNamespace).\n417:         Delete(ctx, sandboxInfo.SandboxName, deleteOpts)\n418: \n419:     return m.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n420: }\n421: ```\n422: \n423: ## Testing Strategy\n424: \n425: ### Unit Tests\n426: \n427: | Test | Coverage |\n428: |------|----------|\n429: | `TestDeleteSandbox` | 正常删除流程、NotFound 处理、K8s 错误处理 |\n430: | `TestCalculateLifecycle` | 从 AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter 获取 timeout 配置 |\n431: | `TestIsExpired` | TTL 过期判断逻辑 |\n432: | `TestIsIdleExpired` | Idle timeout 过期判断逻辑 |\n433: | `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce` | GC 单次运行逻辑 |\n434: \n435: ### Integration Tests\n436: \n437: | Test | Coverage |\n438: |------|----------|\n439: | `TestDeleteSandboxIntegration` | 在 test env 中创建 Sandbox CR 并删除 |\n440: | `TestGarbageCollectorIntegration` | 启动 GC goroutine，验证定期清理 |\n441: \n442: ### Mock/Fake Clients\n443: \n444: ```go\n445: type MockStore struct {\n446:     sandboxes map[string]*types.SandboxInfo\n447: }\n448: \n449: type MockAgentCubeClient struct {\n450:     agentRuntimes    map[string]*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n451:     codeInterpreters map[string]*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n452: }\n453: \n454: // Use client-go fake clientset\n455: func NewFakeAgentCubeClient() *AgentCubeClient {\n456:     clientset := agentcubeclient.NewSimpleClientset()\n457:     return &AgentCubeClient{clientset: clientset}\n458: }\n459: ```\n460: \n461: ### Test File Structure\n462: \n463: ```\n464: pkg/workloadmanager/\n465: ├── lifecycle_test.go         — LifecycleManager 单元测试\n466: ├── garbage_collector_test.go — GarbageCollector 单元测试\n467: ├── deletion_handler_test.go  — HTTP handler 测试\n468: ├── integration_test.go       — 使用 fake client + mock store 的集成测试\n469: ```\n470: \n471: ## Validation Checklist\n472: \n473: - [ ] 删除 Sandbox CR 时同步清理 store 中的记录\n474: - [ ] NotFound 错误不阻塞删除流程（视为已删除）\n475: - [ ] GC 定期清理 expired + inactive sandboxes\n476: - [ ] 删除操作有 timeout 保护\n477: - [ ] Force delete 作为 fallback 机制\n478: - [ ] 与 agentd idle cleanup 不冲突（agentd watch Sandbox CR，workload manager 删除 store 记录）\n479: \n480: ## Open Questions\n481: \n482: - [已解决] GC interval: `2 * time.Minute` (参考 defaults.go)\n483: - [已解决] GC batch size: 16 (参考 sandbox-orchestration design)\n484: - [已解决] Deletion timeout: `30s` (参考 defaults.go `SandboxDeleteTimeout`)\n485: - 是否需要 deletion finalizer 处理？\n486: - 是否需要支持 graceful shutdown period（GracePeriodSeconds > 0）？\n487: \n488: ## References\n489: \n490: - client-go spec: `.sdd_prompt.md` (deployment/client-go.md)\n491: - Source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/pkg/workloadmanager/`\n492: - sandbox-orchestration design: `sandbox-orchestration/design.md`\n493: - idle-cleanup design: `idle-cleanup/design.md`\n494: - shared_types.go: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` (Labels/Annotations constants)\n495: - defaults.go: `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` (Timeout constants)\n\n(End of file - total 495 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n实现 Sandbox 删除处理器及生命周期管理机制，包括：\n- 删除 Sandbox CR 及关联资源（Pod、ServiceAccount 等）\n- TTL 过期清理、Idle timeout 检测、Max session duration 限制\n- Garbage Collector 定期清理失效 Sandbox\n- 与 agentd 的 idle cleanup 协调\n\n## Design\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/design.md","time":{"start":1775846208984,"end":1775846209015}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846209021,"sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","part":{"id":"prt_d78aeb21c001nguXd8DUZ4Zakc","messageID":"msg_d78ae7b9500168dmDFvioVDWFX","sessionID":"ses_28751a2d8ffecSNMhM59C6FXsB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0a69457c34a546e28e2dbf8c02490727","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Store Interface Extensions\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Add `ListExpiredSandboxes` method to Store interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n20:   - Signature: `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n21:   - Verify: `grep -q \"ListExpiredSandboxes\" pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n22: \n23: - [ ] **T1.2** Add `ListInactiveSandboxes` method to Store interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n24:   - Signature: `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n25:   - Verify: `grep -q \"ListInactiveSandboxes\" pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n26: \n27: - [ ] **T1.3** Create mock Store implementation for testing in `pkg/workloadmanager/mock_store.go`\n28:   - Implement all Store interface methods with map-backed storage\n29:   - Implement ListExpiredSandboxes filtering by ExpiresAt < before, limit results\n30:   - Implement ListInactiveSandboxes filtering by LastActivity < before, limit results\n31:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n32: \n33: - [ ] **T1.4** Create tests for mock Store in `pkg/workloadmanager/mock_store_test.go`\n34:   - Test ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired sandboxes only\n35:   - Test ListInactiveSandboxes returns inactive sandboxes only\n36:   - Test limit parameter respects batch size\n37:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestMockStore -v`\n38: \n39: ### Phase 2: LifecycleConfig & Types\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` - LifecycleConfig struct\n42:   - Define LifecycleConfig struct with fields:\n43:     - `DefaultTTL time.Duration` (default: 8h)\n44:     - `DefaultIdleTimeout time.Duration` (default: 15m)\n45:     - `DefaultMaxDuration time.Duration` (default: 8h)\n46:     - `GCInterval time.Duration` (default: 2min)\n47:     - `GCOnceTimeout time.Duration` (default: 2min)\n48:     - `DeletionGracePeriod int64` (default: 0)\n49:     - `DeletionTimeout time.Duration` (default: 30s)\n50:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type LifecycleConfig struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n51: \n52: - [ ] **T2.2** Create `DefaultLifecycleConfig()` function in `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n53:   - Return LifecycleConfig with values from defaults.go constants\n54:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func DefaultLifecycleConfig\" pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.3** Create tests for LifecycleConfig in `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n57:   - Test DefaultLifecycleConfig returns correct values\n58:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestLifecycleConfig -v`\n59: \n60: ### Phase 3: SandboxLifecycleManager Core\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` - SandboxLifecycleManager struct\n63:   - Define SandboxLifecycleManager struct with fields:\n64:     - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n65:     - `store Store`\n66:     - `config LifecycleConfig`\n67:     - `logger Logger`\n68:   - Verify: `grep -q \"type SandboxLifecycleManager struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n69: \n70: - [ ] **T3.2** Create `NewSandboxLifecycleManager` constructor in `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n71:   - Signature: `NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient *K8sClient, store Store, config LifecycleConfig, logger Logger) *SandboxLifecycleManager`\n72:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func NewSandboxLifecycleManager\" pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T3.3** Implement `DeleteSandbox` method in `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n75:   - Steps:\n76:     1. Get sandbox info from store (return NotFoundError if not found)\n77:     2. Delete Sandbox CR via dynamic client using SandboxGVR\n78:     3. Delete SandboxClaim if Kind == \"SandboxClaim\"\n79:     4. Delete from store\n80:   - Use metav1.DeleteOptions with DeletionGracePeriod\n81:   - Handle apierrors.IsNotFound as success (already deleted)\n82:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*DeleteSandbox\" pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n83: \n84: - [ ] **T3.4** Implement `IsExpired` method in `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n85:   - Signature: `IsExpired(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) bool`\n86:   - Return `time.Now().After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`\n87:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*IsExpired\" pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n88: \n89: - [ ] **T3.5** Implement `IsIdleExpired` method in `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n90:   - Signature: `IsIdleExpired(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, idleTimeout time.Duration) bool`\n91:   - Return false if LastActivity.IsZero()\n92:   - Return `time.Now().After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`\n93:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*IsIdleExpired\" pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n94: \n95: - [ ] **T3.6** Implement `ForceDeleteSandbox` method in `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n96:   - Use GracePeriodSeconds=0 for immediate deletion\n97:   - Delete from store regardless of CR deletion result\n98:   - Verify: `grep -q \"func.*ForceDeleteSandbox\" pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n99: \n100: - [ ] **T3.7** Create tests for Dele